## How requests flow
| URL | In production (Vercel) | In dev (`npm run dev:all`) |
|---|---|---|
| `/` (and any non-API route) | static SPA from `dist/`, falls back to `index.html` via `vercel.json` rewrite | Vite dev server on `:5173` |
| `/api/*` | `api/[...slug].js` serverless function → Express app | Vite proxies to `:3000` running `api/_local-dev.js` (same Express app) |

The Express app inside the function is mounted **with the `/api/` prefix** because Vercel forwards `req.url` with the prefix intact. Local dev keeps full parity.

## REST surface (under `/api`)
| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET  | `/api/health` | – | uptime probe |
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | – | create user (status `PENDING`) |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | – | bcryptjs verify → JWT + sanitized user |
| GET  | `/api/users` | admin | list all users |
| PATCH| `/api/users/:id/status` | admin | approve / reject (sends Resend email on APPROVED) |
| DELETE | `/api/users/:id` | admin | cascade-delete user + predictions |
| PATCH| `/api/users/:id/bet` | self/admin | update tournament bet |
| GET  | `/api/predictions` | user | `?userId=`, `?userId=&matchId=`, or `?matchIds=1,2,3` |
| POST | `/api/predictions` | user | upsert one prediction |
| GET  | `/api/scores` | user | leaderboard (cheap — just reads `users.scores`) |
| POST | `/api/scores/recalculate` | admin | re-tally from finished matches; optional tournament bonuses |
| GET  | `/api/football/matches` | user | all WC 2026 matches, normalized shape, cached 60 s |
| GET  | `/api/football/matches/today` | user | matches kicking off today (UTC), normalized shape |
| GET  | `/api/football/teams` | user | all WC 2026 teams (for the Tournament Winner dropdown) |

## Scoring rules (single source of truth: `api/_lib/scoring.js`)
| Outcome | Points |
|---|---|
| Exact score, total goals ≤ 4 | 3 |
| Exact score, total goals ≥ 5 | 5 |
| Correct result (winner/draw), wrong score | 1 |
| Wrong result | 0 |
| Tournament Winner (admin sets actual at tournament end) | 15 |
| Top Scorer | 5 |
| Top Assist | 5 |

## Environment variables
Set these in `.env` locally and in **Vercel project settings** for production.

| Name | Where | Required |
|---|---|---|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | server | yes |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | server | yes |
| `JWT_SECRET` | server | yes |
| `SPORTSDB_API_KEY` | server | optional — defaults to the public free key `123` (30 req/min). Register at thesportsdb.com for a private free key, or pay $9/mo for premium V2 (livescores) |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | server | optional (no-op when blank) |
| `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` | server | optional |
| `CLIENT_ORIGIN` | server | optional — locks CORS in prod |
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | browser | optional — leave blank to use same-origin `/api` |

The browser **must never** see `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SPORTSDB_API_KEY` (even though the default `123` is public), `RESEND_API_KEY`, or `JWT_SECRET`.

## Conventions every agent must follow

### Frontend
- All user-visible text goes through `useTranslation()` and lives in both `locales/en.json` AND `locales/he.json`. **Never** add a key to one without the other.
- Use logical CSS properties (`margin-inline-start/end`, `padding-inline-*`, `inset-inline-*`) so layouts flip cleanly in RTL. Avoid `margin-left/right` unless the side is intentionally physical.
- Date/time formatting: `toLocaleDateString(locale, …)` where `locale = i18n.resolvedLanguage === 'he' ? 'he-IL' : 'en-GB'`.
- Reuse: `AuthContext` (auth + users + scores), `serverApi` (axios with JWT + 401 handler), `useMatches` (session-cached schedule), `useTodayMatches` (smart polling).
- CSS Modules only — no global classes, no Tailwind, no styled-components.
- Mantine components must work in RTL — `MantineDirectionSync` already wires this; do not duplicate.

### Backend (Vercel functions)
- Files under `api/` are **CommonJS** (`require`/`module.exports`) — `api/package.json` enforces this. Files under `src/` are ESM.
- Never call `createClient()` at module load. Use the lazy `supabase` Proxy from `api/_lib/supabase.js`.
- Every TheSportsDB call MUST go through `fetchUpstream(url)` in `api/_lib/football.js` so it shares the 60 s cache + single-flight registry. Never call `axios.get('https://www.thesportsdb.com/...')` directly from a route file.
- All external football data is normalized server-side via `transformEvent` / `transformTeam` in `api/_lib/football.js`. **Route handlers never leak TheSportsDB field names (`idEvent`, `strHomeTeam`, etc.) to the browser** — the frontend speaks the internal shape (`{ id, utcDate, status, stage, homeTeam: { name, crest, … }, score: { home, away, fullTime }, … }`).
- Errors: throw or `next(err)`. The central handler in `_lib/errorHandler.js` sanitizes DB errors to a generic message; route-level errors with `err.status` pass through.
- Auth: `requireAuth` first, `requireAdmin` second (it relies on `req.user`).
- Users can only mutate their own data unless admin — every protected route enforces this server-side, even if the client already filtered.

### PWA
- Icons live in `public/`; the manifest is generated by `vite-plugin-pwa` from `vite.config.js`. To regenerate after replacing the source icon, run:
  ```
  powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/resize-icons.ps1
  ```
- The service worker explicitly excludes `/api/*` from navigation fallback, so dynamic backend calls always reach the network.

### Adding a route
1. Backend: append to (or create) the relevant file under `api/_routes/` and mount it in `api/_app.js`. Always pass `requireAuth` (and `requireAdmin` where appropriate).
2. Frontend: add a method on `serverApi`, then call it from a hook or component. Translation keys for new UI strings go in BOTH locale files.
3. Document the new endpoint in this control file's REST surface table.

## Known follow-ups (pick these up as they unblock)
- **`TOP_SCORERS_LIST` and `TOP_ASSISTS_LIST` are intentionally empty arrays** in `src/utils/constants.js`. The Profile page dropdowns AND the `TopScorersPage` both read from these lists. The owner will paste the final names; agents must not invent them.
- TheSportsDB **WC 2026 fixtures may still be partial** in the free tier — the bracket fills in as FIFA finalizes draws. `AllGamesPage` shows a "Schedule Not Available Yet" empty state if the season returns no events.
- **`MatchCard.IN_PLAY` / `PAUSED` states will not appear on TheSportsDB free V1.** Anything that depends on live in-play status (the dormant `LiveScoreBanner`, the "Live!" badge inside `LiveBetsReveal`) only lights up if the project ever moves to TheSportsDB V2 (premium $9/mo). `LiveBetsReveal` itself still works — it now reveals predictions when a match becomes `FINISHED`.
- The admin must run **POST `/api/scores/recalculate`** after tournament end with `{ tournamentWinner, actualTopScorer, actualTopAssist }` to award the 15/5/5 bonus points. The HomePage admin panel exposes this UI.

## Hard "do not"s
- Do **not** re-introduce the deleted `server/` Express folder or any non-Vercel host.
- Do **not** install `bcrypt` (native) — the project uses `bcryptjs`.
- Do **not** hard-code English (or Hebrew) strings in JSX. Use `t('key')`.
- Do **not** call TheSportsDB from the browser — always go through `/api/football/*`. The frontend has no business knowing field names like `idEvent` or `strHomeTeam`.
- Do **not** re-introduce a generic pass-through proxy at `/api/football/*`. The proxy is intentionally narrow: a handful of typed, normalized endpoints so the upstream schema can be swapped without touching the frontend.
- Do **not** invent player names for `TOP_SCORERS_LIST` / `TOP_ASSISTS_LIST`. The owner supplies them.
- Do **not** add a new top-level dependency without first checking whether existing libs (Mantine, axios, react-router) already cover the need.
- Do **not** edit the front-matter `description` of this file or the "Your role" / "What this app is" sections without explicit owner approval — those are product intent, not implementation detail.
